    effortless-ntwf:activePeriod "1956" ;
    effortless-ntwf:affiliation "UCLA" ;
    effortless-ntwf:keyContribution "Developed the Common Cause Principle (1956): every statistical correlation has a causal explanation, either direct causation or a common cause. This principle frames the paradox as a symptom of an uncontrolled common cause." ;
    effortless-ntwf:signatureWork "Reichenbach (1956) — The Direction of Time" ;
    effortless-ntwf:relationToHannanPearl "Pearl's backdoor criterion is a formalisation of Reichenbach's common-cause screening-off idea in DAG language" ;
